Mix flour, baking soda, cream of tartar, and ground nutmeg. In a separate bowl, cream butter, adding the sugar gradually. Add three well beaten eggs and vanilla extract. Mix in dry ingredients. Wrap dough in plastic wrap and chill in refrigerator. Roll out dough and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 425 degrees F (220 degrees C) for 6 to 8 minutes. Frost and decorate, as desired.